node.text:
PLEASE REPOST THIS ON YOUR STORY
•
TURKEY IS ON FIRE! This needs to be brought to EVERYONE'S attention! More than 60 wildfires have broken out across 17 provinces on Turkey’s Aegean and Mediterranean coasts this week, killing at least 4 people along with thousands of farm animals (SWIPE TO LEARN MORE) #prayforturkey #wildfire #wildfires #staysafeeveryone

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Plant A Tree Co. on July 30, 2021. May be an image of fire, sky and text that says 'TURKEY IS ON FIRE SWIPE'.

Photo by Plant A Tree Co. on July 30, 2021. May be an image of sky and text that says 'More than 60 wildfires have broken out across 17 provinces on Turkey's Aegean and Mediterranean coasts this week, killing at least 4 people along with thousands of farm animals and sending 60 more people to the hospital as their homes burned down வ்கி்்ன் က် ជញ ചോടት'.

Photo by Plant A Tree Co. on July 30, 2021. May be an image of fire, outdoors and text that says 'So far, 18 villages have been evacuated and 35 aircrafts, 457 vehicles and 4,000 personnel have been involved in the firefighting efforts, as separate wildfires raged in the provinces of Osmaniye, Kayseri, Kocaeii, Adana, Mersin and Kutahya.'.

Photo by Plant A Tree Co. on July 30, 2021. May be an image of outdoors and text that says 'Turkey has battled a series of disasters caused by extreme weather conditions this summer, including flash floods last week that killed 6 people in the Black Sea region. These disasters have been devastating to the wildlife in Turkey, killing countless innocent animals and destroying their homes'.
Photo by Plant A Tree Co. on July 30, 2021. May be an image of outdoors.

node.text:
PLEASE REPOST THIS ON YOUR STORY
•
⚠️GRAPHIC IMAGES⚠️ This needs to be brought to EVERYONE’S attention! MBR Acres in Cambridgeshire is a government ran breeding ground for over 2000 Beagles where they are then taken to labs to be experimented on, tortured and killed everyday. (SWIPE TO LEARN MORE)
•
Please sign the petition in our bio

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Plant A Tree Co. on July 15, 2021. May be an image of dog and text that says 'WHAT IS THE MBR ACRES BREEDING GROUND SWIPE >> WARNING: GRAPHIC CONTENT'.

Photo by Plant A Tree Co. on July 15, 2021. May be an image of dog and text that says 'Thousands of dogs are being bred at a factory farm in Cambridgeshire for excruciating experiments. New and deeply upsetting- footage by Stop Huntingdon Animal Cruelty shows whimpering beagles being forced into overcrowded crates, some just by the scruff of the neck, to be taken away and transported to labs across the country that will perform painful experiments on "man's best friend".'.

Photo by Plant A Tree Co. on July 15, 2021. May be an image of dog and text that says 'The beagles from this factory farm are no different from the playful, intelligent, and loving dogs that we welcome into our families. Yet government figures show that dogs were used in 4,227 disturbing procedures in 2019- -4,055 of them involving beautiful beagles.'.

Photo by Plant A Tree Co. on July 15, 2021. May be a black-and-white image of dog and text that says 'Experimenters often administer drugs, pesticides, or other toxic chemicals by gavage this means they inserta force-feeding tube down the dog's throat so chemicals can be pumped into the stomah on a daily basis. Instead of receiving love and affection these dogs will experience side effects such as vomiting, tremors, and raised temperatures At the end of the test, experimenters will kili and dissect the dogs.'.
Photo by Plant A Tree Co. on July 15, 2021. May be an image of 1 person, dog and text that says 'Belong Here Not Here'.
Photo by Plant A Tree Co. on July 15, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'END ANIMAL EXPERIMENTS!'.

node.text: Hundreds of dead sea creatures have begun washing up in Sri Lanka, just weeks after a cargo ship carrying dangerous chemicals caught fire and sank. (Swipe to learn more)

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Plant A Tree Co. on July 08, 2021. May be an image of tortoise, outdoors and text that says 'HUNDREDS OF DEAD SEA ANIMALS WASH UP IN SRI LANKA SWIPE>>'.

Photo by Plant A Tree Co. on July 08, 2021. May be an image of outdoors and text that says 'BBNES Ð NEWS Hundreds of dead sea animals have washed up in Sri Lanka, weeks after a cargo ship carrying dangerous chemicals caught fire and sank. E The X-Press Pearl sank in early June off the coast of Colombo after it had been on fire for days.'.

Photo by Plant A Tree Co. on July 08, 2021. May be an image of body of water and text that says 'BBNES NEWS The remains of 176 turtles, 20 dolphins and four whales have washed ashore since, a court has heard. Experts fear the ship which carried tonnes of oil in its tanks, will remain an environmental hazard for decades.'.

Photo by Plant A Tree Co. on July 08, 2021. May be an image of outdoors and text that says 'BBC NEWS The X-Press Pearl had had been carrying 278 tonnes of bunker fuel oil and 50 tonnes of gas oil when it caught fire on 20 May. was also carrying 25 tonnes nitric acid, along with other chemicals and cosmetics. One environmental group had earlier said the ship's toxic cargo threatened to create 'a chemical soup" in the area.'.

Photo by Plant A Tree Co. on July 08, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'NEWS Our oceans and marine life deserve much better than this and it is our responsibility that change is made. Please share this post with your followers and tag people, celebrities, influencers and news media who need to see this.'.
Photo by Plant A Tree Co. on July 08, 2021. May be an image of one or more people, outdoors and text that says 'HELP OUR MARINE LIFE REPOST ON YOUR STORIES TO RAISE AWARENESS FOR MARINE LIFE'.
Photo by Plant A Tree Co. on June 27, 2021. May be an image of ‎text that says '‎LETS TALK ABOUT YEMEN ㅇ人פ SWIPE >>‎'‎.

node.text: More than two million children under five in Yemen do not have enough food to eat, with over 2,200 on the brink of starving to death. LETS HELP THESE CHILDREN❤️🌲🌎

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Plant A Tree Co. on June 27, 2021. May be an image of ‎text that says '‎LETS TALK ABOUT YEMEN ㅇ人פ SWIPE >>‎'‎.

Photo by Plant A Tree Co. on June 27, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'Yemen is the largest humanitarian crisis in the world, with around 21 million people in need of humanitarian assistance, including more than 11 million children.'.
Photo by Plant A Tree Co. on June 27, 2021. May be an image of 8 people, people standing, outdoors and text that says 'In Yemen, a child dies every 10 minutes from preventable causes'.

Photo by Plant A Tree Co. on June 27, 2021. May be an image of child and text that says 'Ever since armed conflict escalated in Yemen in March 2015, the country has been edging toward social and economic collapse. Eighty percent of the population 24 million people, including roughly 12 million children are in need of humanitarian assistance.'.

Photo by Plant A Tree Co. on June 27, 2021. May be an image of child and text that says 'Increasing food insecurity has pushed the country to the brink of famine. Cholera is endemic. Over 2 million children are malnourished. At least 2 million children have been driven from their homes by violence.'.

Photo by Plant A Tree Co. on June 27, 2021. May be an image of one or more people and text that says 'The COVID-19 pandemic has only compounded the country's suffering, further straining an already fragile health system, disrupting education for millions of children and leaving them increasingly vulnerable to exploitation and abuse.'.

Photo by Plant A Tree Co. on June 27, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'UNICEF's humanitarian strategy focuses on delivering direct, lifesaving assistance and system strengthening. The needs have never been more acute.'.
Photo by Plant A Tree Co. on June 27, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'HELP YEMEN'S CHILDREN REPOST ON YOUR STORIES το RAISE AWARENESS FOR YEMEN'.
Photo by Plant A Tree Co. on June 18, 2021. May be an image of outdoors and text that says 'PLASTIC POLLUTION IS KILLING SEA TURTLES HERE'S WHY >>'.

node.text: Plastic in our oceans is killing countless sea turtles everyday. It’s time to bring this to an end!

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Plant A Tree Co. on June 18, 2021. May be an image of outdoors and text that says 'PLASTIC POLLUTION IS KILLING SEA TURTLES HERE'S WHY >>'.

Photo by Plant A Tree Co. on June 18, 2021. May be an image of body of water and text that says 'Imagine you're in your kitchen and as you approach the countertop your absolute favorite snack appears right in front of you. It looks just like food, it basically smells like food, so you grab it and gulp it down. This happens to sea turtles every day when they consume plastic debris in the ocean.'.

Photo by Plant A Tree Co. on June 18, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Why do sea turtles eat plastic? Plastic bags look very similar to jellyfish, fishing nets often look like tasty seaweed. Sea turtles think they're consuming some of their staple foods when really they're welcoming harmful substances into their digestive tract.'.

Photo by Plant A Tree Co. on June 18, 2021. May be an image of outdoors and text that says 'What does plastic pollution do to sea turtles? Ingesting plastics isn't a harmless mistake, the consumption of this man-made material can cost sea turtles their lives. That's because plastic can cause blockages in their intestines and even pierce the intestinal wall causing internal bleeding'.
Photo by Plant A Tree Co. on June 18, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'STOP KILLING SEA TURTLES REPOST ON YOUR STORIES TO RAISE AWARENESS AND SAVE THE F SEA TURTLES'.
Photo by Plant A Tree Co. on June 15, 2021. May be an image of tree and text that says 'Thank You for IM Followers! SWIPE TO SEE OUR JOURNEY PLANT PLANTATREE TREE'.
